text: Mac OS X Jaguar (version 10.2) is the third big release of macOS, Apple's desktop and server operating system. It superseded Mac OS X 10.1 and preceded Mac OS X Panther. The operating system was started on August 24th, 2002. It was available both for single-computer installations and in a "family pack" that allowed five installations on separate computers in one household. Jaguar was the first Mac OS X release to publicly use its code name in marketing and advertisements. == References == Category:MacOS Category:Apple software
title: Mac OS X 10.2
